 and to triangular\n$L_{\\infty}$-bialgebroids. We also develop a quantum version (for the bosonic\ncase), whose relation with the classical version is like that of the\nSchr\\\"odinger equation with the Hamilton--Jacobi equation. We show that the\nnonlinear pullbacks by microformal morphisms are the limits at $\\hbar\\to 0$ of\ncertain \"quantum pullbacks\", which are defined as special form Fourier integral\noperators.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Nov 2014 03:49:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 18 Jan 2015 03:39:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2015 20:03:31 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 22 Jul 2017 23:35:55 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 17 Sep 2017 18:58:41 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 4 Jan 2018 17:49:25 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Sun, 8 Jul 2018 04:18:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-08"}
