 that is independent of magnetic-field\nstrength. In this case, ions could be accelerated to much higher energies. A\nsearch for $^{44}$Ti emission in the 67.9 keV line results in an upper limit of\n$1.5 \\times 10^{-5}$ $\\,\\mathrm{ph}\\,\\mathrm{cm}^{-2}\\,\\mathrm{s}^{-1}$\nassuming a line width of 4.0 keV (1 sigma).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Nov 2014 07:12:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
